import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_return'] = data['adjclose'].pct_change()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='daily_return', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['daily_return'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['daily_return'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the trend of the stock\'s closing price over time?')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='volume', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['volume'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Volume: {:.2f}'.format(data['volume'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the volume of trading over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
